afw-deploy

Deploy a DAG to the dev Airflow sandbox via fzf picker.

Can be invoked from anywhere inside the project — the function
walks up from $PWD looking for the first directory that contains
both airflow_manager/ and pyproject.toml (typically `.../airflow/`
in the orchestration repo) and cds there before proceeding.

USAGE
  afw-deploy

WHAT IT DOES
  1. Walks up from $PWD to find the project root (a directory
     containing both airflow_manager/ and pyproject.toml) and
     cds there. Aborts if no such ancestor exists.
  2. Verifies that "poetry run afw" resolves to a binary inside the
     project's poetry virtualenv (not a stray afw on $PATH). If the
     venv is missing afw, runs "poetry install" automatically once;
     if afw is still not in the venv after that, aborts with a
     three-line diagnostic (expected venv, resolved afw, project dir).
  3. Opens an fzf picker over *.py files in airflow_manager/dag_folder/.
     Entries are grouped, newest first within each group:
       - locally edited (uncommitted vs HEAD)      — yellow, on top
       - touched in this branch (vs the merge-base
         / fork-point with origin/HEAD)            — green, below
       - everything else                           — default color
     Within each group, files are sorted by mtime (newest first).
  4. Deploys the selected DAG:

       poetry run afw sandbox deploy \
         -e dev \
         -b europe-west1-sdp-composer-91ff48c9-bucket \
         -s ecerulm \
         -d <selected-dag.py>

PICKER LAYOUT
  Each fzf line is a tab-separated record with hidden sort-key
  columns (group, -mtime) and a display column plus a raw-path
  column. fzf's --delimiter=$'\t' --with-nth=3 shows only the
  colored display column; the raw path is read back from the 4th
  field, so no ANSI strip-on-readback is needed. The group column is
  0 = locally edited, 1 = branch-touched, 2 = unchanged. If the working
  directory is not a git repo, or the default branch / merge-base
  can't be determined, the grouping / color-highlight pass is skipped
  and the picker still works (sorted by mtime only).

LAST SELECTION
  The last DAG chosen for each project root is cached in
  ~/.cache/afw-deploy/. On subsequent runs fzf's query is pre-filled
  with the previous selection, so pressing Enter redeploys it instantly.

Requires: poetry, fd, fzf, git.
